*2022-23






            Interprofessional Collaboration with Other Health Professions
          Heading link



 
Copy link






The College is part of the UIC Health Sciences Campus which includes the Colleges of Medicine and Nursing.  Being so closely associated with the other colleges on campus leads to unique interprofessional education opportunities in Rockford.
The campus is located on 20 tree-lined acres.  The facilities include auditoriums, state of the art classrooms and conference rooms with live video conferencing capabilities, teaching and research laboratories, modern compounding and dispensing labs, counseling rooms, patient and mannequin simulation centers, media services, a gym, student lounge and study space, and the Crawford Library of Health Sciences.



      Learn More about the UIC Health Sciences Campus - Rockford
    



      Learn More about Rockford
    








