                            Pharmacy Faculty honored at UIC Faculty Awards reception
                    

                Thursday, October 27, 2022
            

                On Wednesday, October 26, 2022 several College of Pharmacy faculty were honored at UIC’s Faculty Awards Ceremony and Reception. The event is hosted by the Office of the Provost, including the Vice Provost…
            












                            UIC College of Pharmacy moves up to #7 in total research funding
                    

                Thursday, June 30, 2022
            

                The UIC College of Pharmacy has moved up two spots to #7 in the national rankings for total research funding, according to the American Association of Colleges of Pharmacy (AACP). The college had a record year of $24.5 million in funding.
            












                            Fordjour Awarded Martin Luther King, Jr. Scholarship
                    

                Tuesday, January 25, 2022
            

                P2 student pharmacist Samuel Fordjour has been awarded the Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Scholarship by the university.
            
















